<p>Here is my problem.<br> I have a razor generated form that has multiple fields but I want email to only be required if the System Admin radio button is clicked.  It is defaulted to system user.</p>  <pre><code>&lt;div class=""&gt;@Html.LabelFor(m =&gt; m.Email)&lt;/div&gt;      &lt;div class=""&gt;           @Html.TextBoxFor(m =&gt; m.Email, new { @class = "form-control required", placeholder = "Email" })           @Html.ValidationMessageFor(m =&gt; m.Email)      &lt;/div&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I even tried removing the "required" after form control and taking out the validation.</p>  <p>I have 2 radio buttons that are generated by razor that have the same    name but different values.</p>  <pre><code>&lt;div class="inline-editor create-user-roles"&gt;     &lt;input id="UserRole" name="UserRole" type="radio" value="System Administrator"&gt;     &lt;input id="UserRole" name="UserRole" type="radio" value="System User"&gt; &lt;/div&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Here is the JQuery function that I am trying to use.  </p>  <pre><code>$('input[name="UserRole"]').on('change', function () {     if ($('input[name="UserRole"]:checked').val() == "System Administrator") {         $('#Email').rules('add', {             required: true, messages: { required: "This field is required" }         });     }     else {         $('#Email').rules('add', {             required: false         });     } }); </code></pre>